{
  "stem": "14292.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was very religious for a long period of time until about-- this whole thing happened.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, the schools-- we went to the local elementary school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And later on, I went to a gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's called Eotvos-- E-O-T-V-O-S.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Eotvos was a very famous Hungarian physicist.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went to a gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A gymnasium means that we were mostly prepared for different schooling.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In other words, in Europe at that time, the-- most people entered the elementary school and had four years of the general school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they had to-- went to some kind of tradesmanship.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then, it was-- other schools were-- it's called 'real,' R-E-A-L.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And those are for engineering, architect, and so on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was in the gymnasium, the people who wanted to go do something different, like law or medicine.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we had-- I had, when I-- because my parents were very much in business and had little time to spend with us when I was a little boy, was-- a young lady came to us.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She was, at that time, 18 years old-- her name is Anna-- who became very important in our life and even then and later.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she was a very devoted Catholic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And was she practically raising me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so we-- I was exposed very much on other-- every Sunday, I was pushed to go to the [LAUGHS] church.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was Friday in a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was a lot of religion for me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But anyhow, in the school, we were together with other individuals.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was some schools, when religion-- let's say Catholics or Protestants or Jewish school-- but I was not in one of those.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Well, during the daytime-- because in Europe and-- I don't know if it still is-- but at that time, religion and state was not separated.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
